7 Circle Packing

Circular packing or circular treemap allows to visualize a hierarchic organization. It is an equivalent of a treemap or a dendrogram, where each node of the tree is represented as a circle and its sub-nodes are represented as circles inside of it.

library(treemap)
data("GNI2014")
head(GNI2014)
packing <- circleProgressiveLayout(GNI2014$population, sizetype='area')
veri<-cbind(country=GNI2014$country, population=GNI2014$population, packing)
dat.gg <- circleLayoutVertices(packing, npoints=50)

ggplot() + geom_polygon(data = dat.gg, aes(x, y, group = id, fill=as.factor(id)), colour = "black", alpha = 0.6) +
  
   geom_text(data = veri, aes(x, y, size=population, label = country)) +
   scale_size_continuous(range = c(1,4)) +
   theme_void() + 
   theme(legend.position="none") +
  coord_equal()

library(tidyverse)
##  Attaching packages  tidyverse 1.3.2 
##  tibble  3.1.8      dplyr   1.0.9
##  tidyr   1.2.0      stringr 1.4.0
##  readr   2.1.2      forcats 0.5.1
##  purrr   0.3.4     
##  Conflicts  tidyverse_conflicts() 
##  dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter()
##  dplyr::lag()    masks stats::lag()
veri1<-GNI2014 %>% group_by(continent) %>% summarise(POP=sum(population))
packing.veri1<- circleProgressiveLayout(veri1$POP, sizetype='area')
veri1<-data.frame(veri1, packing.veri1)
dat.gg1 <- circleLayoutVertices(packing.veri1, npoints=50)

ggplot() + geom_polygon(data = dat.gg1, aes(x, y, group = id, fill=as.factor(id)), colour = "black", alpha = 0.6) +
  
   geom_text(data = veri1, aes(x, y, size=POP, label = continent)) +
   scale_size_continuous(range = c(1,4)) +
   theme_classic() + 
   theme(legend.position="none") +
  coord_equal()

library(viridis)
## Loading required package: viridisLite
library(ggiraph)

veri1<-GNI2014 %>% group_by(continent) %>% summarise(POP=sum(population))
veri1$text<-paste("name: ",veri1$continent, "\n", "value:", veri1$POP, "\n", "You can add a story here!")
packing.veri1<- circleProgressiveLayout(veri1$POP, sizetype='area')
veri1<-data.frame(veri1, packing.veri1)
dat.gg1 <- circleLayoutVertices(packing.veri1, npoints=50)


p=ggplot() + 
  geom_polygon_interactive(data = dat.gg1, aes(x, y, group = id, fill=id, tooltip = veri1$text[id], data_id = id), colour = "black", alpha = 0.6) +
  scale_fill_viridis() +
  geom_text(data = veri1, aes(x, y, label = gsub("Group_", "", continent)), size=2, color="black") +
  theme_void() + 
  theme(legend.position="none", plot.margin=unit(c(0,0,0,0),"cm") ) + 
  coord_equal()
